@Andy | Eco  @Henry  |  Eco  @Hen | Eco  @Dave | Eco @Sergey (ICO Drops)
Hey!
I want to tell you about a little adventure. Me and @Corleone  decided to make an eco logo on bicycles. We laid out the route and planned to create a clip.
The next day we met at the starting point. Before the trip, we decided to shoot a couple of frames for the video, but as soon as we got ready to go, it started raining. We had to hide from him and wait. It took 30 minutes and we were able to start the journey! We drove sometimes stopping to check the route or shoot frames for a video. Everything went well (despite the mud after the rain). When we started to "draw" the letter o in my bike, something began to knock. At first I did not attach this importance, but then the pedals stopped spinning. We stopped to find out the reason. It turned out that the rear derailleur was bent a lot, and the bike no longer rode normally. We decided to end our journey on foot. An hour later we reached the end point and the word eco appeared on the map! But that was not all. Coming home and opening the received videos, we saw that they were spoiled. The camera did not focus and the image floated terribly. It was impossible to mount. And so the idea was born to write this story and create another video. It's right below my post and it comes out very atmospheric. I will also attach a screenshot from the bike trip.
In the end, I would like to say never give up! Thanks for attention 🙂

Hello everyone!
I present to you my video dedicated to Bounty 015 Gps!
Moscow Night TAXI ECO 283 Km Race!

To complete the Bounty task with GPS, I found a taxi driver who kindly agreed to 
a very unusual ride. The trip was carried out at night with very heavy rain!

The trip took 4 hours and another 2 hours to prepare and organize.
Eco logo track - 283 km. The total mileage, including test trips, is 320 km.
I spent about 6 hours in the car. I finished the task in the morning!

While editing the video, I noticed an amazing moment. 
The ECO icon was on the speedometer!!! And on the right, the text AUTO HOLD!
It happened completely by accident! It was a sign!

I will be happy to Like it.
